title: Zoomies
body:
Lucy the kitten, the Mitochondria of the apartment, has the zoomies this morning. It’s adorable.  I hear quiet, then I find her eyes and she is staring at me with her little butt shaking and then kablam!  She’s on my shoulder from across the room in 0.02 seconds.  

I was going to the bathroom, (sorry, gross) and she jumped up on my shoulder and then began to crawl down my back.  I couldn’t reach her, so I was stuck sitting there and she was stuck because there was no where to go.  It was a fun moment, lol.  Finally, I held my arm out and she used it as a bridge to jump to the bath tub.  

Kitten watch complete:)

I’m having a great time popping in and out of the Livestream for @phandomwatches for @phandomgives for Dan’s birthday to Young Minds.  Have you been?   It’s super fun.  There are raffles and prizes and such.  You should check it out!


I got my new CPAP mask and it is the wrong size…but I can make it work by adjusting the straps.  I need a small (which is weird) but they sent me a medium.  

Kitten watch update: Lucy is current EATING her scratching bed.   I mean, I GUESS that’s okay? lol

I had weird dreams last night, but thankfully, I don’t remember them.


I finished “Heavy”, which is a very intimate book about an African American man and is a memoir in the form of a letter to his mother.   It’s excellent.  

I’m now listening to “Maybe You Should Talk to Someone” and it’s just great. It’s about a therapist who needs therapy, and is also a memoir.  

I’m going to take a nap. Maybe my mask didn’t fit as well as I thought it did, lol. I sleeeepy:)

Have a great day!!!
